paper_metadata.extraction_summary: The paper discusses various mutations in BRCA1 and BRCA2 genes in the context of ovarian cancer treatment with olaparib. However, only one BRCA2 variant was identified.

patients.phenotype: bilateral high grade serous ovarian cancer, stage IV with liver metastasis

individual_records.phenotype_details: bilateral high grade serous ovarian cancer, stage IV for liver metastasis
individual_records.evidence_sentence: The molecular characterization revealed: a c.425+2T>C (IVS4+2T>C) intronic variation of the BRCA2 gene.

functional_data.summary: The variant is predicted to affect or create splice donor or splice acceptor sites.

variants.additional_notes: This variant was considered likely pathogenic based on its predicted effects on splicing.
key_quotes: a c.425+2T>C (IVS4+2T>C) intronic variation of the BRCA2 gene. This substitution was considered likely pathogenic because it was predicted to affect or create splice donor or splice acceptor sites.
